FBIS3-1740 "drchi040_k_94019" FBIS-CHI-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Mar 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Radio To Air Some `Program One' Casts in Stereophonic Sound OW2602055594 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in Mandarin 2230 GMT 25 Feb 94 OW2602055594 Beijing Central People's Radio Network Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [From the "News and Press Review" program] [Text] Listeners. As a result of continued progress in broadcasting, recording, and media technology, effective 1 March, the Central People's Radio Network will air casts under Program One, that have been originally broadcast via frequency 106.1 MHz, in stereophonic instead of monophonic sound system. While being broadcast in stereophonic sound system, casts -- especially literary casts -- in the Central People's Radio Network Program One will have characteristics such as treble and bass notes, a strong sense of reality, and a pleasant timbre to provide listeners with more melodious entertainment.
